quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  36,28,"And We sent not down upon his people after him any hosts from heaven, nor do We need to send"
  36,29,"It was naught but a single Shout, and lo! They were still and silenced (extinct)"
  36,30,Alas for the servants! There comes not to them a messenger but they mock at him
  36,31,"Do they not consider how many of the generations have We destroyed before them, because they do not turn to them (the messengers) (or which return not unto the people)"
  36,32,And all of them shall surely be brought before Us
  36,33,"And a sign to them is the dead earth: We give life to it and bring forth from it grain so they eat of it"
  36,34,And We make therein orchards of palms and grapevines and We make springs to flow forth in it
  36,35,"that they may eat of the fruit thereof, and their hands did not make it; will they not then be grateful"
  36,36,"Glory be to Him Who created pairs of all things, of what the earth grows, and of their kind and of what they know not"
  36,37,"And a sign to them is the night: We draw forth from it the day, then lo! They are in the dark"
  36,38,"And the sun runs on to a term appointed for it; that is the ordinance of the Mighty, the Knowing"
  36,39,"And as for the moon, We have ordained for it stages till it becomes again as an old dry palm leaf"
  36,40,"Neither is it allowable to the sun that it should overtake the moon, nor can the night outstrip the day; and all float on in their own orbits"